https://teamtreehouse.com/library/practice-the-css-box-model


All HTML elements are rectangular boxes... 

In CSS, each of these rectangular boxes is described using the standard box model. This model describes the space of the content taken by an element. Each box has four edges: the margin edge, border edge, padding edge, and content edge.


Inner Box is the Content, then Padding, Border, and finally Margin

Margin
   |
Border
   |
Padding
   |
Content



If the CSS box-sizing property is set to default, the CSS properties:
    width, min-width, max-width, 
    height, min-height and max-height 
control the content size.


The space between the padding and the content edge can be controlled using:
    padding-top, padding-right, padding-bottom, padding-left 
    and the shorthand padding CSS 
    
The size of the margin area is controlled using:
    margin-top, margin-right, margin-bottom, margin-left 
    and the shorthand margin CSS properties
    
    
The total width of an element calculation:

        width + left padding + right padding + left border + right border + left margin + right margin

The total height of an element calculation:

        height + top padding + bottom padding + top border + bottom border + top margin + bottom margin